Katy Perry is the latest performer to be added to the Grammy Awards lineup.The Recording Academy made the announcement on Twitter, saying the pop star has been confirmed to take the stage this weekend.According to Billboard, Perry is expected to premiere a new song called &#8220;Chained to the Rhythm&#8221; featuring Skip Marley.Other performers include Beyonce, The Weeknd, Daft Punk, Adele, John Legend, Metallica, Carrie Underwood, Bruno Mars, Keith Urban, John Legend, Anderson .Paak, A Tribe Called Quest and others.The 59th annual Grammy Awards airs Feb. 12 on CBS.-Relaxnews